OK i got the solution, but i have changed the approach.
here the new code. I also added some responsiveness to slider. Now instead of z-index, i check the margin-left to animate the slider container and not only 1 slide at time, so i don&#39;t have to know whitch is te current slide to find the next one, i just care about if margin is less than 0 and more than the difference between the `.slide` width and the `.slider-wrapper` width. In this way when you click on the left i subtract to the margin-left the current `.slide` width and add it when right is clicked. Take a look at `resize_slider()` function. Last thing but not for relevance putting `.stop()` before `.animate()` prevents overlapping of animations.
