For using RXJS operators(like map, filter, etc...), you need to use `pipe()` method for every operator and put all operators you would like to use inside `pipe()` method. So, operators are not methods as it was introduced in RXJS 5.5.

For example:

    of(1,2,3).pipe(
      map(x =&gt; x + 1),
      filter(x =&gt; x &gt; 2)
    );

Old way looked like this (now it doesn&#39;t work):

    of(1,2,3).map(x =&gt; x + 1).filter(x =&gt; x &gt; 2);

